HEADWORD: Trickish
<hw>Trick"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Given to tricks; artful in making
bargains; given to deception and cheating; knavish.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Trick"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Trick"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trickle</ent>⟦br⟧
